  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "To add a link to another Quora answer within your answer using the Quora iPhone app, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Quora App**: Make sure you are logged into your account.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Answer You Want to Link**: Find the Quora answer you want to reference in your own answer. Tap on the answer to open it fully.\n\n3. **Share the Answer**: Tap the \"Share\" icon (it looks like an arrow coming out of a box) usually located at the top right corner of the answer.\n\n4. **Copy Link**: From the share options, select \"Copy Link\" to copy the URL of the answer to your clipboard.\n\n5. **Go Back to Your Answer**: Navigate back to the question where you are writing your answer.\n\n6. **Paste the Link**: Tap on the text field where you are composing your answer. When the keyboard appears, tap and hold on the text field, then select \"Paste\" to insert the copied link into your answer.\n\n7. **Format the Link (Optional)**: If you want the link to appear as clickable text rather than a full URL, you can format it like this: `[Text you want to show](URL)`. For example, if the URL you copied is `https://www.quora.com/Some-Question/Some-Answer`, you can write `[See this answer](https://www.quora.com/Some-Question/Some-Answer)`.\n\n8. **Submit Your Answer**: Once you're satisfied with your answer and the link, tap \"Post\" or \"Submit\" to publish your answer.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully add a link to another Quora answer within your own answer using the Quora iPhone app.",
